@Greg AP Sometimes clients will want a website built from the ground-up because what they request is something services like Squarespace or Wordpress can't offer so you have to go old school. Even if SS offers great templates, sometimes creating your own to meet the custom needs of the clients will be more preferable. 

Big corporations like Amazon, McDonald's, Netflix, Walmart, etc. likely don't use website builders because they likely require everything from scratch from the front-end to the back-end like databases. For a small business in a local area, you could use templates. It all depends on your clients' needs. 

Also, it's pretty cool and fulfilling to have the skills to build a website by hand. I gained a boost in confidence building some clones like Steam and Windows XP which I'm currently working on.
